1000
01:47:08,280 --> 01:47:10,710
I wouldn't blame you.

1001
01:47:10,950 --> 01:47:14,140
Who's your CO?

1002
01:47:14,350 --> 01:47:16,980
It would've been Captain Jennings.

1003
01:47:17,190 --> 01:47:20,310
I'm afraid the best we can muster up now is a corporal.

1004
01:47:21,760 --> 01:47:24,730
So what are you guys all about?

1005
01:47:24,960 --> 01:47:28,450
We're here for him. Ryan.

1006
01:47:28,700 --> 01:47:30,530
Me, sir?

1007
01:47:39,470 --> 01:47:42,710
James Francis Ryan of lowa?

1008
01:47:42,910 --> 01:47:48,040
Yes, sir. Peyton,Iowa, that's correct. What is this about?

1009
01:47:50,080 --> 01:47:52,780
Your brothers were killed in combat.

1010
01:47:59,760 --> 01:48:01,700
Which ones?

1011
01:48:04,270 --> 01:48:06,560
All of them.

1012
01:48:14,580 --> 01:48:17,200
On the level?

1013
01:48:18,550 --> 01:48:21,910
Yeah, I'm afraid so.

1014
01:48:23,180 --> 01:48:25,120
You might want to take some time with this.

1015
01:48:25,350 --> 01:48:28,620
If there's someplace you want to go and...

1016
01:48:37,400 --> 01:48:40,230
-What's this all about?  -Ryan lost his brothers.

1017
01:48:40,440 --> 01:48:43,460
-Which one?  -All of them.

1018
01:48:51,780 --> 01:48:54,480
You came all the way out here to tell me that?

1019
01:48:56,850 --> 01:49:00,080
You're going home.

1020
01:49:00,290 --> 01:49:03,020
Our orders are to bring you back.

1021
01:49:06,530 --> 01:49:08,720
Bring me back?

1022
