He loses his shovel. It goes out of his grasp and hits a kerosene lantern.

1217
02:05:59,330 --> 02:06:04,930
The thing explodes. The whole barn almost goes up because of this thing.

1218
02:06:19,020 --> 02:06:22,350
That was it, that was the last... Dan went off to Basic the next day.

1219
02:06:22,550 --> 02:06:26,220
That was the last night the four of us were together.

1220
02:06:26,420 --> 02:06:28,450
That was two years ago.

1221
02:06:30,560 --> 02:06:32,620
Oh, my.

1222
02:06:33,730 --> 02:06:38,430
Tell me about your wife and those rose bushes.

1223
02:06:38,640 --> 02:06:43,540
No. No, that one I save just for me.

1224
02:07:49,110 --> 02:07:50,770
Enemy from the east.

1225
02:07:52,440 --> 02:07:57,000
He sees two Tiger tanks, two Panzer tanks.

1226
02:07:57,250 --> 02:08:01,150
Infantry. 50 plus change.

1227
02:08:10,030 --> 02:08:13,020
Disperse! You know what to do. Reiben, get on the rabbit.

1228
02:08:13,260 --> 02:08:17,500
Upham, get some cover. Mellish and Henderson, lock and load!

1229
02:08:17,700 --> 02:08:20,190
Everybody check your ammo!

1230
02:08:20,440 --> 02:08:25,100
-Good luck,Reiben!  -I don't need any luck,I was born lucky!

1231
02:08:38,160 --> 02:08:41,490
One in five tracer. Yes, and tracers point both ways.

1232
02:08:41,690 --> 02:08:44,960
Why don't you check the head space and she should run.

1233
02:08:53,370 --> 02:08:56,240
Upham, hustle up!

1234
02:09:45,990 --> 02:09:49,890
Corporal Upham. We don't have a.30 calibre machine gun here.

1235
02:09:50,090 --> 02:09:55,550
Either Mister Mellish or Mr Jackson in the bell tower needs that.

1236
02:09:55,800 --> 02:09:58,860
Upham! Jackson's fine, turn around to Mellish!

1237
02:10:20,390 --> 02:10:24,120
There's a ton of infantry. I don't know if they took the bait, though.

1238
02:10:48,250 --> 02:10:50,520
Have you got any more of that?

1239
02:11:36,330 --> 02:11:38,560
The Panzers didn't take the bait.

1240
02:11:43,610 --> 02:11:46,340
The infantry's moving to the left.

1241
02:11:46,540 --> 02:11:49,710
A half-track just went by with about 20 troops.

1242
02:13:28,710 --> 02:13:32,380
Mellish, Henderson! Displace!

1243
02:13:53,500 --> 02:13:57,410
Do it, now! Light it up! You! Light it!

1244
02:14:08,720 --> 02:14:13,090
30 infantry on the right flank. Get over there, find a hole and stop them!

1245
02:14:13,290 --> 02:14:15,760
Displace!

1246
02:14:26,600 --> 02:14:28,370
Upham!

1247
02:14:43,150 --> 02:14:46,090
Clear! OK, go!

1248
02:14:46,320 --> 02:14:48,050
Krauts!

1249
02:14:49,660 --> 02:14:51,890
Right flank!

1250
02:15:27,560 --> 02:15:30,430
Get down, get down!

1251
02:15:36,840 --> 02:15:39,970
Upham! Thirty cal, hurry!

1252
02:15:40,180 --> 02:15:43,410
Find the Captain, this flank's going to fold!

1253
02:16:38,400 --> 02:16:40,800
Traversing! He's still in this fight!

1254
02:16:42,310 --> 02:16:44,870
No! Ryan, get down, get down!

1255
02:16:57,750 --> 02:16:59,980
Ryan!

1256
02:17:18,240 --> 02:17:20,040
Ryan!

1257
02:17:21,340 --> 02:17:23,640
Keep your mouth shut Get off me!

1258
02:17:23,850 --> 02:17:25,580
-Are you alright?  -Get off of me!

1259
02:17:25,780 --> 02:17:28,250
I'm fine too, Captain. Thanks.

1260
02:17:28,480 --> 02:17:32,940
Hit them from both sides. Get aboard! Get a grenade in there!

1261
02:17:36,990 --> 02:17:38,430
Grenade!

1262
02:17:40,200 --> 02:17:43,130
20 mill! 20 mill!

1263
02:17:43,330 --> 02:17:44,990
Flak gun, 20 mm. Take it out!

1264
02:17:58,450 --> 02:18:01,850
Heavy weapon in defilade below! I ain't got a shot!

1265
02:18:06,390 --> 02:18:10,720
Pincer move! Parker! Targets eight o'clock, low!

1266
02:18:10,930 --> 02:18:13,020
God grant me strength.

1267
02:18:26,480 --> 02:18:29,640
Let's go, displace! Come on!

1268
02:18:46,030 --> 02:18:49,230
Cover! Upham, cover!

1269
02:19:05,450 --> 02:19:07,510
I'm out of.30 calibre.

1270
02:19:10,950 --> 02:19:13,480
Blessed be the Lord my strength, which teaches my hands to war -

1271
02:19:13,720 --> 02:19:16,060
and my fingers to fight.

1272
02:19:24,670 --> 02:19:29,090
My goodness and my fortress. My high tower and deliverer.

1273
02:19:32,510 --> 02:19:35,240
My shield and He in whom I trust.

1274
02:19:38,820 --> 02:19:40,840
Here you go, baby.

1275
02:20:03,440 --> 02:20:05,660
Parker, get down!

1276
02:20:26,820 --> 02:20:29,130
Captain, that 20 mm is killing us.

1277
02:20:29,330 --> 02:20:33,880
-We've got to try to flank it somehow.  -Let me get over there for a top shot.

1278
02:20:59,130 --> 02:21:01,060
Upham!

1279
02:21:19,350 --> 02:21:24,210
Upham, Upham! Upham, ammo, goddammit!

1280
02:22:07,330 --> 02:22:11,150
-I'm jammed! Got any.30 calibre?   -I'm out.

1281
02:22:23,240 --> 02:22:25,680
Upham. Upham!

1282
02:23:18,360 --> 02:23:19,920
Reiben!

1283
02:23:23,460 --> 02:23:24,660
Reiben!

1284
02:23:51,820 --> 02:23:56,160
I'm out! I need another bandolier. Anybody got a bandolier?

1285
02:24:27,360 --> 02:24:29,420
You piece of shit!

1286
02:25:13,970 --> 02:25:19,070
Let's stop, let's stop! Listen to me! Stop! No, no, no...

1287
02:25:45,870 --> 02:25:47,630
Fuck!

1288
02:25:55,480 --> 02:25:59,980
Son of a bitch, son of a bitch!

1289
02:26:00,220 --> 02:26:02,310
Son of a bitch!

1290
02:27:23,700 --> 02:27:28,110
I'm out! Those.60 rounds...

1291
02:27:28,310 --> 02:27:31,170
-We can use them without the tube.   -How?

1292
02:27:31,380 --> 02:27:34,640
Fuse-arming wire, set back and heave it!

1293
02:27:49,960 --> 02:27:52,360
Panzer schreck!

1294
02:28:09,480 --> 02:28:11,470
Go, go!

1295
02:28:25,930 --> 02:28:28,460
We're going to the Alamo.

1296
02:28:38,340 --> 02:28:40,610
Alamo! Alamo!

1297
02:28:59,830 --> 02:29:03,320
We'll take it. You fall back! You be right behind us!

1298
02:29:03,570 --> 02:29:05,500
As soon as we're in business.

1299
02:29:09,610 --> 02:29:12,040
Displace. Reiben!

1300
02:29:14,310 --> 02:29:16,340
Reload!

1301
02:30:04,530 --> 02:30:06,000
Alright, go!

1302
02:30:07,170 --> 02:30:10,070
We're blowing the bridge! Get off! Off the bridge!

1303
02:30:34,160 --> 02:30:37,030
Sarge! Mike, are you alright?

1304
02:30:37,230 --> 02:30:39,630
-I just got the wind knocked out of me.  -Let's go!

1305
02:30:39,830 --> 02:30:42,730
Take cover, we're going to blow this bridge!

1306
02:30:44,670 --> 02:30:46,400
Come on!

1307
02:30:51,110 --> 02:30:53,440
Tiger company's coming across the bridge.

1308
02:31:26,180 --> 02:31:29,380
Captain, get behind something!

1309
02:31:55,210 --> 02:31:56,970
Mike!

1310
02:32:01,750 --> 02:32:03,510
Mike!

1311
02:32:45,990 --> 02:32:50,050
Captain, where the hell are you going? Captain, get back here!

1312
02:34:43,180 --> 02:34:44,610
Upham!

1313
02:35:14,270 --> 02:35:16,400
Hang in there.

1314
02:36:01,790 --> 02:36:03,760
Medic!

1315
02:36:06,360 --> 02:36:09,020
Medic! We've got a medic?

1316
02:36:15,670 --> 02:36:19,360
They're tankbusters, sir. P-51s.

1317
02:36:19,570 --> 02:36:21,660
Angels on our shoulders.

1318
02:36:27,680 --> 02:36:29,770
What, sir?

1319
02:36:33,820 --> 02:36:35,880
James...

1320
02:36:37,120 --> 02:36:39,250
Earn this.

1321
02:36:42,830 --> 02:36:45,190
Earn it.

1322
02:37:13,530 --> 02:37:16,790
"My dear Mrs Ryan."

1323
02:37:17,000 --> 02:37:20,930
"It's with a profound sense of joy that I write to inform you"

1324
02:37:21,170 --> 02:37:25,470
"that your son, Private James Ryan, is well"-

1325
02:37:25,670 --> 02:37:30,440
"and at this moment on his way home from European battlefields."

1326
02:37:30,640 --> 02:37:34,810
"Reports indicate that James did his duty in combat"

1327
02:37:35,010 --> 02:37:38,040
"with great courage and steadfast dedication"

1328
02:37:38,280 --> 02:37:42,780
"even after he was informed of the loss your family has suffered"

1329
02:37:43,020 --> 02:37:47,960
"in this great campaign to rid the world of tyranny and oppression."

1330
02:37:48,190 --> 02:37:51,130
"I take great pleasure injoining the Secretary of War, "

1331
02:37:51,360 --> 02:37:56,300
"the men and women of the US Army, and the citizens of a grateful nation"

1332
02:37:56,540 --> 02:38:02,570
"in wishing you good health and many years of happiness with James."

1333
02:38:02,810 --> 02:38:07,270
"Nothing, not even the safe return of a beloved son"

1334
02:38:07,510 --> 02:38:11,510
"can compensate you or the thousands of other American families"

1335
02:38:11,750 --> 02:38:15,050
"who have suffered great loss in this tragic war."

1336
02:38:15,250 --> 02:38:17,150
"I might share with you some words"-

1337
02:38:17,360 --> 02:38:22,820
"which have sustained me through nights of peril, loss and heartache, "

1338
02:38:23,060 --> 02:38:27,050
"and I quote, 'I pray that our heavenly Father"

1339
02:38:27,300 --> 02:38:30,600
"may assuage the anguish of your bereavement"

1340
02:38:30,800 --> 02:38:34,640
"and leave you only the cherished memory of the loved and lost"

1341
02:38:34,840 --> 02:38:37,210
"and the solemn pride that must be yours"

1342
02:38:37,410 --> 02:38:42,680
"to have laid a so costly a sacrifice upon the altar of freedom."

1343
02:38:42,880 --> 02:38:44,850
"Abraham Lincoln."

1344
02:38:45,080 --> 02:38:47,550
"Yours very sincerely and respectfully,"

1345
02:38:47,790 --> 02:38:51,120
"George C. Marshall. General, Chief of Staff."

1346
02:39:42,210 --> 02:39:47,200
My family is with me today. They wanted to come with me.

1347
02:39:50,280 --> 02:39:55,620
To be honest with you, I wasn't sure how I would feel coming back here.

1348
02:39:57,920 --> 02:40:03,660
Every day, I think about what you said to me that day on the bridge.

1349
02:40:05,500 --> 02:40:09,830
I've tried to live my life the best I could.

1350
02:40:10,040 --> 02:40:13,060
I hope that was enough.

1351
02:40:13,310 --> 02:40:17,640
I hope that at least in your eyes...

1352
02:40:17,840 --> 02:40:21,780
l've earned what all of you have done for me.

1353
02:40:35,090 --> 02:40:37,120
James.

1354
02:40:38,660 --> 02:40:41,690
"Captain John H. Miller."

1355
02:40:49,370 --> 02:40:54,310
-Tell me I have led a good life. -What?

1356
02:40:54,550 --> 02:40:56,910
Tell me I'm a good mess.

1357
02:41:04,020 --> 02:41:06,080
You are.

